## 4️⃣ เรื่อง uint32_t vs uint64_t ⚠️

### **ปัญหาที่ต้องระวัง:**

```javascript
// Current POGLS uses JavaScript numbers (double precision)
// But when converting to C/Rust/embedded:

// uint32_t = 32 bits = 0 to 4,294,967,295
const MAX_UINT32 = 0xFFFFFFFF;  // ~4.2 billion

// For N_BITS = 20:
// Single coordinate: 20 bits (max = 1,048,576) ✅
// Packed (x,y,z): 20 + 20 + 20 = 60 bits ❌ OVERFLOW!

// Example collision:
const point1 = { x: 500000, y: 500000, z: 0 };
const point2 = { x: 0, y: 0, z: 500000 };

// If using uint32_t incorrectly:
// Both might hash to same value due to overflow!
```

### **วิธีแก้:**

```javascript
// Option 1: ใช้ uint64_t เมื่อ N_BITS > 10
class SafeCoordinatePacking {
  constructor(N_BITS) {
    this.N_BITS = N_BITS;

    // Calculate required bits
    const totalBits = N_BITS * 3;  // x, y, z

    if (totalBits <= 32) {
      this.useUint32 = true;
      console.log("Using uint32_t (safe)");
    } else if (totalBits <= 64) {
      this.useUint64 = true;
      console.log("Using uint64_t (safe)");
    } else {
      throw new Error(`N_BITS=${N_BITS} requires >64 bits!`);
    }
  }

  packCoordinates(x, y, z) {
    if (this.useUint32) {
      return (x | (y << this.N_BITS) | (z << (this.N_BITS * 2))) >>> 0;
    } else {
      // Use BigInt for uint64_t
      return (
        BigInt(x) |
        (BigInt(y) << BigInt(this.N_BITS)) |
        (BigInt(z) << BigInt(this.N_BITS * 2))
      );
    }
  }
}

// Option 2: ใช้ separate hash per axis (ปลอดภัยกว่า)
class SeparateAxisHashing {
  hashPoint(x, y, z) {
    return {
      x_hash: this.hash32(x),
      y_hash: this.hash32(y),
      z_hash: this.hash32(z)
    };
  }

  hash32(value) {
    // MurmurHash3 or xxHash (32-bit safe)
    value = Math.imul(value ^ (value >>> 16), 0x85ebca6b);
    value = Math.imul(value ^ (value >>> 13), 0xc2b2ae35);
    return (value ^ (value >>> 16)) >>> 0;
  }
}
```

### **ตารางเปรียบเทียบ:**

| N_BITS | Total Bits | uint32 ✅/❌ | uint64 ✅/❌ | แนะนำ |
|--------|-----------|------------|------------|-------|
| 8      | 24        | ✅ Safe    | ✅ Safe    | uint32 |
| 10     | 30        | ✅ Safe    | ✅ Safe    | uint32 |
| 12     | 36        | ❌ Overflow | ✅ Safe    | uint64 |
| 16     | 48        | ❌ Overflow | ✅ Safe    | uint64 |
| 20     | 60        | ❌ Overflow | ✅ Safe    | uint64 |
| 21+    | 63+       | ❌ Overflow | ⚠️ Risky   | Separate |

